WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.210 --> 00:00:04.320
- Can you get big with bands?

00:00:04.320 --> 00:00:06.240
See that question all the time?

00:00:06.240 --> 00:00:07.920
A lot of people make
declarative statements.

00:00:07.920 --> 00:00:12.060
Either you can or can't
get big with bands.

00:00:12.060 --> 00:00:13.770
Now, I'm gonna give you the truth here.

00:00:14.760 --> 00:00:19.170
Bands absolutely suck if you're using them

00:00:19.170 --> 00:00:20.670
by themselves.

00:00:20.670 --> 00:00:22.260
The problem with a band,

00:00:22.260 --> 00:00:26.490
and I have one here, show
you if I'm gonna do a pushup

00:00:26.490 --> 00:00:29.190
with a band, and let's say
I throw it around my back

00:00:29.190 --> 00:00:32.250
and I go to get on the floor
in pushup position holding the

00:00:32.250 --> 00:00:36.240
band like this, the
problem is my hand is going

00:00:36.240 --> 00:00:40.020
to outwardly rotate because
the van wants to be a circle.

00:00:40.020 --> 00:00:41.790
The more tension you put on
it, the more it wants to be in.

00:00:41.790 --> 00:00:43.350
Its just natural shape.

00:00:44.520 --> 00:00:47.220
It's gonna twist your
joints, it's gonna hurt you.

00:00:47.220 --> 00:00:50.370
You won't even be able to load

00:00:50.370 --> 00:00:52.680
properly in the stronger position.

00:00:52.680 --> 00:00:55.500
But most importantly,
the stretched position,

00:00:55.500 --> 00:00:57.660
the down position, that's

00:00:57.660 --> 00:01:00.810
where the most muscular stimulus happens.

00:01:00.810 --> 00:01:05.220
I know there's been a lot of
guys, kind of the, the guru

00:01:06.240 --> 00:01:08.880
internet PhD guys who've
been talking about lengthened

00:01:08.880 --> 00:01:12.000
partials and the importance
of lengthened partials.

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:14.250
I, I think they've definitely over hyped

00:01:14.250 --> 00:01:16.170
that issue, but they're not wrong.

00:01:17.280 --> 00:01:20.340
Any set of anything that anyone ever did,

00:01:20.340 --> 00:01:22.500
the stimulus happened at the bottom.

00:01:22.500 --> 00:01:24.270
That's where you go to fatigue.

00:01:24.270 --> 00:01:27.510
So you don't want to ignore
that position with a band.

00:01:27.510 --> 00:01:29.850
You can't load that position.

00:01:29.850 --> 00:01:32.700
Like it's just awkward and it hurts.

00:01:32.700 --> 00:01:36.420
So bands by themselves suck.

